title: Moving Day
body:
Oh my gosh it’s been a hot minute since I’ve written. This was an anonymous request I received a while ago. Finally got some inspiration to write it! Chris Evans x reader

Warnings: None




“This is the last of it babe.” You hear your boyfriend say as he brings in the last box into his bedroom.

Actually now it was your room too. That was going to take some getting used to. After dating Chris for over a year, he asked you to move to Boston with him. It was overwhelming leaving your old life behind in Ohio, but you were more than happy with your decision to move in with him. Being in a long distance relationship was hard, especially with his career. Luckily, you were able to find a good paying job in your field that would allow you to travel with Chris more too. Things were falling into place slowly but surely.

“Thanks hun. That won’t take me long to unpack, it’s just my toiletries and makeup. Then I’ll be officially all moved in.” You smile as you break down another box and drop in into the pile of the others.

“I’m gonna call for a pizza and open a bottle of wine to celebrate.”

“Sounds absolutely perfect.” You say as you grab the last box. “I’m gonna grab a quick shower after I unpack this.”

“Take your time baby. I’m going to take Dodger for a quick walk before the food gets here. Be back shortly.” He says as he pecks your cheek then heads downstairs.

You head to the bathroom and open the last box. Thankfully, there wasn’t much inside. Just the last of your makeup, and skincare products. Relief washed over you when you broke down the last box. Finally, you were able to shower and relax with your man. The hot water felt superb against your tense muscles. After packing the moving van, driving for two days, and unpacking, exhaustion was hitting you hard. Once you finished cleaning the past forty-eight hours off your body, you grab one of Chris’s shirts and a pair of panties and make your way down to the living room. Chris and Dodger were still out on their walk, so you crawled onto the couch and turned the TV on while you waited. Your eyes were growing heavier by the second, but you continued to fight to stay awake.

Your head turned towards the door when you heard your boys return from their walk. Dodger jumped right on the couch and gave you kisses. You giggled and rubbed his back. “Hey there buddy did you have fun with daddy?”

“He had a blast.” Your boyfriend smiles as he bends down to drop a kiss on your lips. “You look good in my shirts.”

“They’re pretty comfy.” You smile as you pull him down to lay with you.

“You okay there baby? I know you’re probably exhausted.” He says as he pulls your legs onto his lap.

“I could honestly fall asleep right now, but I’m starving.”

“Well the food will be here soon baby, and then we can go to bed.”

“It’s so early though.” You whine. “I wanted to celebrate our first night officially living together.”

“We’ve got plenty of time to celebrate my love I promise. Tonight let’s just relax and unwind.”

“Alright.” You agree as you hear the doorbell. You go to get up to answer but Chris stops you.

“No offence babe, but I’m not letting you answer the door when you’re not wearing pants.”

You blush and look down, realizing you forgot you were half-naked in your sleep-deprived state. “I bet I wouldn’t have to leave a tip though.” You tease.

“Not a chance I’d let you try babe.” He laughs as he runs to the door to pay the delivery person. He comes back a couple minutes later with pizza and wine. “Dig in.”

You devour two slices in a matter of five minutes and go to grab a third when Chris is barely finished with his first slice. “I’m sorry babe you have no idea how hungry I’ve been. I haven’t eaten since I stopped at that creepy truck stop in Pennsylvania this morning.”

“Don’t apologize Y/N. Why didn’t you tell me sooner? I would have ordered the food earlier.”

“I didn’t want to stop unpacking.” You said. “If I took a break before it would have been game over.”

“Well you’re all moved in now and we have the entire week to ourselves. So let’s toast to that.” He smiles as he holds his wine glass up.

You smile and clink your glass against his. “I love you.”

“I love you too Y/N.”

After you finished your third slice, you collapsed back onto the couch and curled up into a ball. Your belly was full, and you hit your peak of exhaustion.

“You ready for bed babe?”

You couldn’t even answer properly from being so tired. “Mmmhmm.”

Suddenly, you felt yourself being lifted into Chris’s arms. You lazily wrapped your arms around his neck and kept your eyes closed, too exhausted to even protest. He laid you gently on the bed and tucked you in. You heard Chris tell Dodger it was bedtime before they both got into bed.

“Come here love.” Chris whispers to you as he holds his arm out.

You happily place your head on his chest and wrap your arms around his torso.

“Goodnight baby. Welcome home.” He says as he places a kiss on the top of your head.

You fall asleep with a small smile on your lips moments later.

summary: "He’s so great. I can’t say enough about him, I really can’t. I didn’t know what to expect going in to work with him. He’s so...
body:
“He’s so great. I can’t say enough about him, I really can’t. I didn’t know what to expect going in to work with him. He’s so talented and he’s got so much charisma and persona. I can honestly say, of all the movie stars I’ve worked with, he’s the one that when he comes on set, you really feel like, ‘Man — this guy’s a movie star!’ You just feel it. When he comes in a room he just owns the oxygen.”

Chris Evans on Robert Downey Jr.

summary: Drabble Inspired by Episode: Chris Evans (feat. Chris Evans)
title: Drabble Inspired by Episode: Chris Evans (feat. Chris Evans)
body:
*In honor of last night’s events, here is a repost of the Chris Evans drabble that was originally posted on January 20th. You’re welcome.*

Chris stands behind me placing his hands on my hips as I brush my teeth. “We’re going,” I say. “We’ll see,” he says. He kisses my neck and I tell him, “It’s not going to work.” It’s an industry party and he really wants to skip it. He promised we’d be there and we’ve already skipped 3 this month. “We have to go,” I remind him.

He drops to his knees and lifts my skirt. As I keep brushing I say, “I told you, it’s not going to work.” I feel his tongue, “I said…” he licks faster. He’s got me and he knows it.

We’re not going to the party.

trail.content:
*In honor of last night’s events, here is a repost of the Chris Evans drabble that was originally posted on January 20th. You’re welcome.*

Chris stands behind me placing his hands on my hips as I brush my teeth. “We’re going,” I say. “We’ll see,” he says. He kisses my neck and I tell him, “It’s not going to work.” It’s an industry party and he really wants to skip it. He promised we’d be there and we’ve already skipped 3 this month. “We have to go,” I remind him.

He drops to his knees and lifts my skirt. As I keep brushing I say, “I told you, it’s not going to work.” I feel his tongue, “I said…” he licks faster. He’s got me and he knows it.

We’re not going to the party.

caption:
HOME | THE PREMISE | DESIGNATIONS | APP FORM | CLAIMS | SKELETONS

                                        Order born from the wrath of chaos

Chicago Illinois, a city rebuilt and protected by PRIME. It is an organization tasked with policing both the Conduit species itself and maintaining the peace between it and mankind. Having bought out the privatized contract for law enforcement throughout all of Chicago; they have kept the peace within the city. Well, for the most part. The Mavericks, a group that has seen PRIME’s methods and control have begun to rebel against the organization. They Are willing to do anything to maintain their freedom and remove PRIME from the city. They are not alone, however, and when motivations within the city collide; everyone has to pick a side, even if its the wrong one.

                                                                                          CHAOS WILL ALWAYS TRIUMPH OVER ORDER

SEQUENCE is a mutant/abilities roleplay. This group contains mature themes and is rated as such. We accept OCs and Skeleton Canon characters. We concern ourselves with our members enjoying themselves having a great place to plot, post and have fun with each other. If this sounds right up your alley, feel free to check us out and ask any questions you might have.

     Accepting within twenty four hours of receiving application!
